> Sorry I don't have time to review right now but I will say that a few days ago I was going to ask on Zulip whether we should use `RelSeries` in `CompositionSeries` ðŸ˜†

No worries, I am not in urgent need of merging this into mathlib4, so take your time.

> We're not adding aliases for the renamed results. Should we?

We can certainly add the aliases, but I doubt they will be useful. The renamed results are mostly implementation details of `CompositionSeries`, so they are not used outside this file anyway.
I aligned the two lemmas again. I think I messed up when dealing with merge conflict

Thanks!

We're not adding aliases for the renamed results. Should we?

This is a great refactor! Thanks for doing it! I've left a couple of comments. The only thing which made me a bit sad is that a couple of proofs got longer because of a random `.toFun` appearing which wasn't there before. If you can figure out why this is happening this would be great, but I don't think it should be a blocker for this PR, and everything else seems to obviously be a step in the right direction.
We're not adding aliases for the renamed results. Should we?

So indeed there does seem to be a global instance of JordanHolderLattice on `Submodule R M`. This seems to contradict line 55 of the TODO suggesting there should be no global instance. Maybe you should add this remark to the TODO?
Added a remark.
It seems to me that this lemma is being removed? Should there be a corresponding lemma about RelSeries?
added the corresponding lemma
Should `RelSeries.toList_ne_empty` be called `RelSeries.toList_ne_nil` then?
changed
Where did you change it? Can't find the change anywhere.
It appears that I messed up git, I have changed them again.
This could be a `dsimp only` (I never quite know whether non-terminal dsimps are OK)
So again you're removing two lemmas completely. Should there be RelSeries versions of these?
there is a similar version in `RelSeries`, similar but not the same. I aligned them anyway and added a note
I'm confused -- they're still #noalign
My bad, I think I messed up this when dealing with merge conflict. I have aligned them again.
It's a shame that you have to do `-smash_toFun` here. Should it not be a simp lemma in general?
yeah, `smash_toFun` shouldn't be a thing. It is removed now

All proofs have got smaller, apart from the last couple and the next couple, which seem to have got bigger because Lean 4 has randomly introduced a `.toFun` which wasn't there before. Can you figure out why this is happening? (I can't!)
I couldn't figure out where the `toFun` comes from. But I managed to shorten the proof by adding other simp lemma anyway
If you like you can get rid of the next porting note now!
thanks
It feels a bit odd to have this theorem which doesn't mention `CompositionSeries` here. Can it go upstream?
moved, thanks
I think one empty line is enough
deleted thanks
Here as well I prefer the `CompositionSeries` name. Can you fix the `RelSeries` name in a future PR?
Should I just do it in this PR?
It might be better to stick to just one job in this PR, it's already +199 lines.

```suggestion
theorem last_eraseLast_le (s : CompositionSeries X) : s.eraseLast.last â‰¤ s.last := by
```

```suggestion
    p.snoc newLast rel (Fin.last (p.length + 1)) = newLast := last_append _ _ _
```
or am I missing something?
Inside some proofs about `CompositionSeries.Equivalent`, there are some `toFun` appeared somehow. This lemmas is meant to fix that.
Aren't you rather missing a general lemma that `f.toFun = f`?
~~I have added `toFun_eq_coe`.~~This lemmas seems still to be necessary, becasue the other lemma `last_def` only deals with `p.snoc newLast rel (Fin.last (p.snoc newLast rel).length)`
Okay, I see what you mean. Can you add a comment that this lemma is only here for simp confluence?
I have added a note

```suggestion
    p.snoc newLast rel (Fin.last (p.length + 1)) = newLast := last_append _ _ _
```
`foo_def` should be of the form `foo = _`, not `_ = foo`
I changed the lemma to `apply_last`

```suggestion
#align composition_series.length_pos_of_mem_ne RelSeries.length_pos_of_nontrivial
#align composition_series.forall_mem_eq_of_length_eq_zero RelSeries.subsingleton_of_length_eq_zero
```
